@page "/graphql"
<br />

<img src="/Images/GraphQL_Logo.svg.png" asp-append-version="true" style="max-width: 400px; max-height:400px;" />

<br />

<div style="width: 80%">
    <MatAccordion Multi="true">
        <MatExpansionPanel>
            <MatExpansionPanelSummary>
                <MatExpansionPanelHeader>Introduction</MatExpansionPanelHeader>
            </MatExpansionPanelSummary>
            <MatExpansionPanelDetails>
                <p>GraphQL is a query language for APIs and a runtime for fulfilling those queries with your existing data.</p>
            </MatExpansionPanelDetails>
        </MatExpansionPanel>
        <MatExpansionPanel>
            <MatExpansionPanelSummary>
                <MatExpansionPanelHeader>Queries</MatExpansionPanelHeader>
            </MatExpansionPanelSummary>
            <MatExpansionPanelDetails>
                <p>GraphQL queries are used to retrieve data from the server. You can modify the retrieve data so you just get what you need to use.</p>
                <br />
                <p><b>Query example: </b></p>
                <pre class="language-graphql">query contracts{
  contracts{
    id
    name
  }</pre>
            </MatExpansionPanelDetails>
        </MatExpansionPanel>
        <MatExpansionPanel>
            <MatExpansionPanelSummary>
                <MatExpansionPanelHeader>Mutations</MatExpansionPanelHeader>
            </MatExpansionPanelSummary>
            <MatExpansionPanelDetails>
                <p>Mutations are like queries but mutations are used for insert, modify or delete data.</p>
                <p>Also you can send the variables using the variable property of the graphQL request instead of adding directly in the mutation as you can see in the following example</p>
                <br />
                <p><b>Mutation example:</b></p>
                <pre>mutation CreateContract{
  createContract(newContract:{name: "Example", contractType: "Local"}){
    id
    name
    contractType
  }
}</pre>
            </MatExpansionPanelDetails>
        </MatExpansionPanel>
        <MatExpansionPanel>
            <MatExpansionPanelSummary>
                <MatExpansionPanelHeader>References</MatExpansionPanelHeader>
            </MatExpansionPanelSummary>
            <MatExpansionPanelDetails>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="https://graphql.org/">Official Page</a>: GraphQL official page</li>
                    <li><a href="https://github.com/graphql-dotnet/graphql-dotnet">GraphQL-DotNet github</a>: GraphQL nuget used in this tutorial</li>
                    <li><a href="https://graphql-dotnet.github.io/docs/getting-started/introduction">GraphQL-DotNet Documentation</a></li>
                </ul>
                <p><b>Other interesting references</b></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="https://www.red-gate.com/simple-talk/dotnet/net-development/building-and-consuming-graphql-api-in-asp-net-core-3-1/">GraphQL tutorial</a></li>                    
                </ul>
            </MatExpansionPanelDetails>
        </MatExpansionPanel>
    </MatAccordion>
</div>

